So first collect them to the same map that you already have. Then sort them by the value; then iterate that result and get _only_ those that are at the very beginning and match their values.

The idea is that since these are already sorted by value: `3 = 2; 4 = 2; 5 = 2; 1 = 1` - we only need to iterate as long as that `2` is repeated, as soon as there is no such match, we are done (because they are sorted and thus any element that follows and `!= 2` is only going to be smaller).

